eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports from Gqeberha. Courtesy of #DStv403 GQEBERHA - Taxi associations in Gqeberha will return to work after week-long protest action. Taxi owners gave the Labour Department seven days to check if COVID-19 relief payments were made. READ: Gqeberha commuters left stranded as taxi drivers protest Taxi operators met with associations on Friday. Meanwhile, the Mayor of the Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality wants to deploy the army to quell taxi violence in the area. Nqaba Bhanga says he's approached the President to approve the move. Taxi operators are angry, saying they've not received any COVID-19 relief funding.